In a call between President Obama and Republic of Korea President Lee Myung-bak, they discussed their reaction to North Korea's nuclear test. Both leaders agreed that the test violated international law and called for action in response. They also agreed to work together to seek a strong United Nations Security Council resolution to limit North Korea's nuclear and missile activities. President Obama reassured President Lee of the United States' commitment to defending South Korea and expressed appreciation for South Korea's decision to join the Proliferation Security Initiative. Additionally, President Obama offered his condolences to the people of Korea for the loss of President Roh Moo-hyun.